g.text: Strength and ductility of the S700MC steel laser beamwelded joints.
Laser welding led to a decrease in tensile strength to approximately 790 MPa in relation to that of
the base material (820 MPa). Similar results were also obtained for MAG welded joints. The rupture
took place in the fusion line area and was accompanied by the formation of a structural notch. The
reduction of tensile strength was connected with the loss of properties obtained by steel S700MC in
the TMCP process. The angle obtained in a bend test amounted to 180
